Bit Rate's Stage.title: Opening Ceremonies
Bit Rate's Stage.description: Join us as we welcome everypony back to our second online event. Learn a little about our staff and get hyped for our incredible lineup of events.

Bit Rate's Stage.title: Concert: PrinceWhateverer
Bit Rate's Stage.description: PrinceWhateverer is a long-standing community musician based in the UK who's been making tunes for the MLP fandom since 2011! He's been performing live at MLP conventions since BonyCon 2013, and has since hit many cons around Europe and the US. He plays predominantly metal and rock music so if you're looking for high volume and high energy, you're in the right place!

Bit Rate's Stage.title: Concert: Inkuma the Bewear
Bit Rate's Stage.description: Ink here! The now-digital artist is back for another live set for everypony to enjoy. EDM music from all over the brony music scene is here to rejuvenate your lovely experience in the fandom!

Bit Rate's Stage.title: Equestria's NEXT Top Artist!
Bit Rate's Stage.panelists: RiffPonies, SilverQuill, Forward Progress, Pirate Dash, ChocoPony, Kevin
Bit Rate's Stage.description: Art is subjective...unless you're drawing ponies, of course! Join the RiffPonies crew and a gaggle of special guest stars as teams of non-artists and popular fan-artists clash for artistic supremacy in a gauntlet of artwork-based games with YOU as the judge! Decide who truly is "Equestria's New Top Artist"!

Bit Rate's Stage.title: More JackBox with the Gang!
Bit Rate's Stage.description: It’s time to goof off! Join in on the fun as ACRacebest, Saberspark, and their friends get together to play JackBox with you, the audience, helping determine who has the best answers!

Bit Rate's Stage.title: I Ship It!
Bit Rate's Stage.description: Shipping's a part of every fandom, but how do you go about it? Love at first sight? Mutual interests? Opposites attract? Join several infamous shippers in a discussion about the various expressions, their possible pitfalls, and why they appeal to fans in the first place.

Bit Rate's Stage.title: My Little Tesla: Behind the Arcs
Bit Rate's Stage.description: The My Little Tesla group has put on demonstrations at over two dozen pony conventions, and you may have even seen one of them yourself. Attend to get a behind-the-scenes look at how we put together demonstrations, how we control the coils, build pictures, stories, never-before-seen footage, and a couple exclusive looks at our BIG tesla coil that throws 10ft arcs!

Bit Rate's Stage.title: A Moment with Lena Hall
Bit Rate's Stage.description: Join Tony Award winner and Grammy nominee Lena Hall, voice of Countess Coloratura, for Q&A and maybe more!

Bit Rate's Stage.title: Riffing Rainbow 2.0: The Fuf Has Been Doubled!
Bit Rate's Stage.panelists: RiffPonies, Simul, Kevin (From TrotCon), Forward Progress, Argembarger, Foal Papers
Bit Rate's Stage.description: More horrible fan-fiction, more horrible people, and an even MORE horribly good time! Join the RiffPonies crew and a cast of special guest stars both old and new as they brave more terrible Pony fan-fiction and force you to read along with them! It's going to be plenty of fuf-...er...fun!

Bit Rate's Stage.title: Why Not Anthology?! - Directors' Commentary
Bit Rate's Stage.description: Welcome to the Anthology Panel! We're a group of editors and animators who have made multiple fan made videos mixing pop culture content with MLP.. Come on by for some fun and interesting commentary on the making of one of our videos!

Bit Rate's Stage.title: Brony Feud! ft. VIPs
Bit Rate's Stage.panelists: Aphinity, M. A. Larson, Amy Keating Rogers, G. M. Berrow, Bill Newton, Vincent Tong, Katrina Salisbury
Bit Rate's Stage.description: Come see a fun gameshow with two teams of VIP guests pitted head-to-head to find the most popular answers to pony themed survey questions!

Bit Rate's Stage.title: Sketches From a Hat
Bit Rate's Stage.description: The classic improv game turned art panel, Sketches From a Hat is at PonyFest Online! Suggest a sketch or scene you'd like to see drawn, drop it into our digital "hat", and our panel of experienced horse artists will do their best to speed draw as many as they can!

Bit Rate's Stage.title: Concert: Forest Rain
Bit Rate's Stage.description: Forest Rain is a transgender Pop/Punk & Alternative musician who makes original music & covers based on cartoons, TV shows, and video games. She shares her passion for music with a love for nature, art, photography, and spicy food! A brony musician since January 2012, Forest is the voice behind "Great to be Different", "Join the Herd" and "Summer in the Stars", creator and producer of "The Massive Smile Project", and co-creator of brony music show Elements of Harmony. She is looking forward to streaming an acoustic set LIVE for everyone at Ponyfest!

Bit Rate's Stage.title: Concert: Rock Fox
Bit Rate's Stage.description: Rock Fox is a trance and hard dance DJ based in Sydney, Australia with a huge passion for music across the breadth of the fandom. They are the current host of The Full Spectrum on Ponyville FM, a weekly show with over 100 episodes dedicated to representing the finest horse music as well as tracks from beyond the fandom! If you've seen Rock Fox behind the decks at Alicon and Vanhoover Pony Expo or a smorgasboard of furcons and club residencies, you know to expect quick fire mixes with a hearty respect for the classics-and for those that haven't, prepare for a trip down memory lane!

Bit Rate's Stage.title: Closing Ceremonies
Bit Rate's Stage.description: Another epic Saturday for the books. Join us for reflections, thanks yous, and special announcements regarding the future of PonyFest Online!

E-Gaming.title: Rocket League Tournament + Smash Bros. Tournament

Neural Net's Stage.title: EU Convention Organizer Panel
Neural Net's Stage.description: Convention staff from across Europe talk shop, discuss the ins and outs of convention work, and answer your questions!

Neural Net's Stage.title: The Brony Chef's Food Challenge
Neural Net's Stage.description: This panel was perfectly aged with a challenge from one of you guys. I'll be cooking it and making it as if I were going to serve it in my own restaurant, so expect quality at all times!

Neural Net's Stage.title: History Of My Little Pony (and the longevity of the fandom)
Neural Net's Stage.description: Come and learn about the history of My Little Pony. From beige beginnings to the pastel ponies we all know and love today.

Neural Net's Stage.title: I'm Not Brony Chef but Bake with Me Anyways ft. CosmicKeyframe
Neural Net's Stage.description: Bored inside? Have a sweet tooth? Come join CosmicKeyframe to satisfy the cravings with some Rainbow Dash themed cupcakes! Cosmic will take you step by step into this simple and fun recipe that is sure to satisfy even the biggest RD hater.

Neural Net's Stage.title: Con Chair Chat with TekCharlie
Neural Net's Stage.description: It takes more than an epic beard and a love of craft beer and ponies to run two MLP cons every year. Join 11-time Con Chair Charlie Worthley to ask anything you'd like about the ins, outs, and oh-what-nows of bringing Ponyville Ciderfest and Whinny City Pony Con to life.

Neural Net's Stage.title: Zootopia Minute LIVE ft. ACRacebest
Neural Net's Stage.description: Zootopia Minute is a podcast examining every detail of the hit 2016 Disney film "Zootopia" one minute at a time. Join hosts Simul and Choco as they review, analyze, and criticize one minute from the film, discussing it's characters, themes, and the wider impact of the film as a whole on fan communities.

Neural Net's Stage.title: MLPT: Mad Lib Pony Theater
Neural Net's Stage.panelists: Nova Rose, Thoth Penswell, Acesential, Forward Progress
Neural Net's Stage.description: It's your favorite moments of MLP like you've never ___(verb)___ them before. Join in the ___(noun)___ as we take your suggestions to fill in the blanks of some of pony's most memorable scenes. You won't believe your ___(noun)___ as we perform these scenes in ___(adjective)___ ways you never expected!

Neural Net's Stage.title: MLP Drawing School's Silly Drawing Hour
Neural Net's Stage.panelists: CutePencilCase, Jenni the Dragon, Pixienop, Cortawsome, Vex, FluffyXai
Neural Net's Stage.description: A few of us silly artists will work together, and create the most amazing OCs, taking body part and characteristic suggestions from the chat!

Neural Net's Stage.title: Tales from a Concert Manager
Neural Net's Stage.description: Luck Rock is the concert lead for HarmonyCon, BABScon, Whinny City, TrotCon, Ciderfest, and more. Come hear about how he works to coordinate talent and concert schedules for the different cons as well as notable stories and more in this interactive panel!

Neural Net's Stage.title: Pony Transformation (in the Canon and Fandom)
Neural Net's Stage.description: Finally, for the first time, a panel that discusses the transformation subculture within the fandom. Join artists Chocolate Pony, Acesential, Daf, and Icaron, as they talk about the instances of transformation and shapeshifting within the show and what elements and tropes appeal to them when drawing such artwork.

Neural Net's Stage.title: The Obligatory All About Them Pony Comics Panel!
Neural Net's Stage.description: It started at HAHcon, then it was at LooneyCon, and now it’s at PonyFest Online! So sit back and have some fuf with ComicSansPony and his fellow comic enthusiasts as they talk everything IDW pony comics.

Neural Net's Stage.title: Drawing4Exposure
Neural Net's Stage.description: A panel of starving artists. A bloodthirsty crowd. Requests drawn in gameshow-style entertainment. MidnightPremiere, Taurson, and Paleheart challenge the audience in a desperate battle of wills. Welcome...to Drawing4Exposure!

Neural Net's Stage.title: Brony Drumming (a History of MLP Percussion)
Neural Net's Stage.description: Ever wanted to find who is behind the percussion of the brony fandom? Join Whirlwind and Drummershy for an inside scoop of brony music with percussion and how we write songs in brony music with drum beats. Plus discussion of the gear we use to incorporate a great sound for brony music.

Writing Room.title: Open Read and Critique (Session 1)
Writing Room.description: Bring the first five minutes of your MLP fanfic (or other story) to this interactive workshop, and get rapid-fire, round-robin feedback on your writing from fellow authors. No prior experience is required.

Writing Room.title: The 5 Steps to Writing Anything like a Pro
Writing Room.description: Raccoon explains her 5 steps for writing anything, from Fanfiction, to Papers, to Emails, in detail.  If you're a new writer looking to learn about basic technique, or an experienced one looking to brush up on the fundamentals, this is the seminar for you!

Writing Room.title: The Universal Engagement Curve
Writing Room.description: Pacing is one of the most important aspects of any work, be it books, movies, or video games. Learn how one squiggly line will keep audiences engaged with your work.

Writing Room.title: Second Person Writing and YOU
Writing Room.description: Love it or Hate it, second person perspective stories have taken the fanfiction community by storm! What is second person? Which stories are the right ones to start reading? Should you try writing it? Where do I even begin? Who are you and how did you get in my house? Well all of those questions will be answered and more by our expert (citation needed) at this panel!

Writing Room.title: Favorite Fanfictions: A Conversation with Writers
Writing Room.panelists: Xepher, BubbleBean, Nyronus, Flutterpriest, Monochromatic, Titanium Dragon, Raccoon
Writing Room.description: Over 10 years, this fandom has 100,000+ published stories, and more than 1.5 BILLION words. It's fair to say that My Little Pony fanfiction has come a long way. Come join some of our guest fanfic authors, as we discuss our favorite stories from this past decade of pony. We'll focus on what makes these stories stand out, and what we, as writers, can learn from them to improve our own skills in the craft.

Writing Room.title: Dark Fantasy: Improving stories through use of Horror Elements
Writing Room.description: As part of this years' Nightmare Night in April, Raccoon gives a seminar and workshop on how to use Horror Elements to improve your stories, in depth and appeal, from concept, to plot, to writing style itself.

Writing Room.title: Why Ponyfic Matters: Transformative Art and the Role of Fanfiction in the MLP Community
Writing Room.description: Wanderer D and Nyronus discuss the role of transformative art in literary history, why My Little Pony: Friendship is Magic produces such notable stories, and the role fanfic plays in the larger community.

Writing Room.title: Character Creation, Evolution, and Development
Writing Room.description: How do we come up with good ideas for characters? How do we change them to fit our expectations? Where do the characters end up? All these questions, and more, Somber will try to answer. They'll probably fail horribly, but they'll try! Come with all your questions and more.

Writing Room.title: Head to Headcanon
Writing Room.panelists: Xepher, BubbleBean, Nyronus, Aquaman, Monochromatic, Somber, Raccoon, Grand Moff Pony
Writing Room.description: Why can't Scootaloo fly? What does Derpy do in her spare time? What's Gummy's secret mission? These questions and less will be answered in this improv game show. Come watch, cheer, and vote as fan-fiction's top minds and willing fools debate on matters suggested by you.

Writing Room.title: Clever Writing, Clever Characters
Writing Room.description: Tyrion, Ender, Minderbinder, Sanchez, Thrawn, Vetinari, Xanatos... we all love them, those clever, scheming masterminds, always one step ahead. But how do you write them as a mere mortal with a normal IQ? Come learn some tips on how to write clever plots and clever characters, without needing a PhD yourself.

Writing Room.title: Pony Break: Speedwritten Scriptwriting by Ponyfic Writers
Writing Room.description:
While the real sequel to the My Little Pony major motion picture may be a ways off, there's no reason we can't brainstorm and outline one of our own in the meantime, right? Provided, of course, we do it off-the-cuff, based on randomized plot elements and guest stars, and all in one hour or less. Because, y'know, we're in a hurry to do so many other things at the moment.

Join FIMFic writers Aquaman, GaPJaxie, and Monochromatic for this improvisational story-breaking session, modeled after the Maximum Fun podcast "Story Break."

Writing Room.title: Open Read and Critique (Session 2)
Writing Room.description: Bring the first five minutes of your MLP fanfic (or other story) to this interactive workshop, and get rapid-fire, round-robin feedback on your writing from fellow authors. No prior experience is required.
